    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>I was just reading this in the book ‘Seth Speaks’. there is SO much more to consciousness than what is defined, agreed, believed and defended or accepted as consciousness, but the identification with it as an independent manipulator of experience – aka ‘myself’ runs – when active in the so called waking state – as if it is in fact in control and defining all things awry to assert itself where it does not belong and is not needed.</p> 
<p>A lot of what we call waking consciousness could be called an interference pattern.<br /> We often identify with the noise – rather than the signal, and then mutually explore the noise to ‘make sense of it’.</p>

